text:
Thank you everyone for the calls, texts, and kind wishes. I’m happy to share that I’m safe, sound, and enjoyed a good dinner this evening.

Each and every day is a blessing.

Have a great Tuesday!

However, we must continue to work diligently to reach an agreement on the full FY24 government spending bills.
 
I thank my colleagues on both sides of the aisle for working with me to pass this bill and keep the federal government open.

(3/3)

This Continuing Resolution is an important stopgap measure to ensure our government can continue providing resources and support to South Texans during these trying times. It also keeps our Border Patrol agents and our troops paid.

(2/3)

Today, I voted to pass a Continuing Resolution that will keep the federal government open for 45 days.
 
Our country is facing many challenges, and we cannot afford to have our government shut down.

(1/3)

Today, I sent a letter to the House requesting my salary be withheld in the event of a government shutdown.

I stand with my 15,575 employees in my district who may miss their paychecks if a shutdown happens.

If they’re not going to get paid, I’m not going to get paid.

I’m deeply saddened to hear that U.S. Senator Dianne Feinstein of California has passed away. Senator Feinstein was a trailblazing public servant and the longest serving female Senator.

Thank you for your service, Senator Feinstein. God bless her and her family.

I met with @coinbase and Texas crypto/blockchain companies, including @TXblockchain_, in my Washington, DC office. It was great to learn about the utility and innovation that cryptocurrency and blockchain offer our country in the Digital Age.

Thanks for stopping by!

G’Mar chatima tova!

Wishing a meaningful and reflective Yom Kippur to all who observe in South Texas.

Thank you to @CBPTroyMiller, Manny Padilla, Secretary Mayorkas and the Mexican government for coming to this agreement, listening to our border communities, and taking action to secure our border.

(3/3)

We need law and order at our southern border. We need consequences at the border. That means playing defense on their 20 yard line instead of our one yard line at the U.S./Mexican border.

(2/3)

The new agreement between the United States and Mexico to deport migrants from Mexican border cities will help stay the recent surge in border crossings.

cnn.com/2023/09/23/us/mexico…

(1/3)

My wife, Imelda, and my daughters, Christina and Catherine, joined me for The Texas Tribune Festival. We had a great time.

I hope everybody has a restful, enjoyable weekend!

My good friend and colleague, @RepTonyGonzales, and I joined the @TexasTribune for a discussion on bipartisan solutions to address our nation’s pressing issues, including avoiding a government shutdown and securing our southern border.

Thank you, Texas Tribune, for hosting us!

This morning, at The Texas Tribune Festival, I sat down with @politico to discuss the opioid crisis.

Thank you to @meganmesserly for hosting an engaging conversation about how we can combat the opioid crisis across our country.

It’s always great to welcome a fellow South Texan to Congress.

Today, I met with @RochelleMGarza, Chair of the U.S. Commission on Civil Rights and President of the Texas Civil Rights Project.
 
Thank you, Rochelle, for all you do in service to South Texas and our country.

It’s time to listen to border communities and readjust current policies to have real consequences at the border.

I remain committed to working with both Democrats and Republicans to secure our Southern border. 

(2/2)

expressnews.com/politics/art…

The current border situation is unsustainable and needs to be addressed. Just over the last two days, 4,000 migrants have crossed into Eagle Pass, Texas. 

Texas is on the front lines of this crisis and we need a secure border now. 

(1/2)

This morning, I joined @cspanMcArdle to give my thoughts on the government funding deadline. It was great to speak with viewers from across the country.

Thank you, John, for having me! You’re a great host and it’s always a pleasure to join you.

Today, I met with @SCMGardner, Ecosystems Division Director at the UN Environment Programme.

Based in Kenya, Susan leads global programmes to support countries to promote nature-based solutions for sustainable development, including for food systems and disaster risk reduction.

My daughter, Christina, surprised me at the office today with cake for my birthday.

Thank you, Christina! I love you.

It was great to meet with @CONCAMIN and @abugaberjose this morning in my Washington, DC office. 

With trade between the United States and Mexico continuing to increase year after year, it’s important that we foster a working relationship that brings our countries mutual success.

Thanks for visiting me today in Washington, DC, @Ron_Nirenberg! I look forward to continuing our work together for San Antonio. 

We’ll see you back in Texas soon.

Happy 76th birthday to the @usairforce! Today, we salute the brave men and women of the Air Force, past and present. 
 
Randolph Air Force Base in San Antonio has been a pillar of strength in defending our nation.
 
Thank you for your dedication and service to our country.

Happy National Hispanic Heritage month!

From September 15 through October 15, we celebrate the cultures and contributions of Hispanic Americans, especially in South Texas.

A Border Patrol Tactical Team (BORTAC) helped capture escaped Pennsylvania killer Danelo Cavalcante.

Thank you to the men and women in green as well as the countless law enforcement personnel who serve our country every day.

amp.cnn.com/cnn/2023/09/13/u…

22 years ago today, 2,977 American lives were lost in terrorist attacks on the World Trade Center.

We will never forget September 11, 2001.

Join me today on #PatriotDay in remembering those we lost, including the many heroic first responders who bravely ran towards danger.

The event culminated in legendary labor leader Linda Chavez-Thompson presenting me a 2023 Retiree Hero award from the @ActiveRetirees for my 100% voting record in support of retired Americans.
I also presented a letter from @VP Kamala Harris thanking the Central Labor Council for extending her an invitation to the breakfast.

This #LaborDay, I joined the @AFLCIOSA for their annual Labor Day Breakfast. It was great to see so many fellow labor advocates.

I gave a keynote address about my work in Congress on behalf of South Texas working families.

Thank you to Reverend Dr. Robert Jemerson and Second Baptist Church for inviting me to Sunday service. It was great to hear the word of God with you along with my good friend, Pastor Patrick Jones.

May the Lord bless you and your church. I hope everyone has a blessed Sunday!

Thank you to:

-> SABCTC President Mark Potter, @UALocal142

-> Shane Denn, @60Ibew

-> Matt Gonzales, @LIUNA Local 1095

-> Gary Aiken, @60Ibew 

-> Glenn Miles, @InsulatorsUnion Local 87

for meeting with me.

I will continue to stand with the working families of South Texas. Just last month, I announced a $1,300,000 earmark for @TheIronworkers Local #66 to provide workforce apprenticeship training for the next generation of ironworkers in San Antonio.
This morning, I met with the San Antonio Building & Construction Trades Council (SABCTC) @TxBldgTrades @NABTU. SABCTC represents the unionized construction industry in the San Antonio region.

Today, my Bexar County Outreach Coordinator, Toro Martinez, attended the ribbon cutting and 2-year anniversary celebration of Bermudas Daiquiris To-Go in Live Oak.

Congratulations to owners James Cooks and Gabriel Ortiz on 2 years of successful business! Here’s to many more.

Today, I also announced $200,000 in Operation Stonegarden funding to support border security in McMullen County.

Thank you to McMullen County Sheriff Emmett Shelton as well as our local, state, and federal officers for their commitment to helping secure our southern border.

This morning, I joined the Laredo Sector Border Patrol, @CBP, @TxDPS, @webb_county, Laredo Police Department, and @unitedisd Police Department for High 5 Friday at Trautmann Elementary. We greeted students with a High 5 as they arrived for school.

Have a great day, Longhorns!

Today, I announced $4,305,000 in federal funds to support border security in Webb County. 

The funds were provided by Operation Stonegarden, a program I helped start in 2008.

I’ll continue to help our local law enforcement agencies keep South Texas communities safe and secure.
I’m deeply saddened to hear that my colleague, @SteveScalise, has been diagnosed with blood cancer. Steve is a fighter, and I know he’ll be back to good health soon. Praying for you, Steve!

This morning, @HHSGov announced the first 10 drugs covered under Medicare Part D that will be eligible for negotiation.

This was made possible by the Inflation Reduction Act, a landmark law that I helped pass last year to bring relief to South Texas Medicare beneficiaries.
Lance Corporal Espinoza’s sacrifices will always be remembered. May he rest in peace, and may God be with his family.

2 years ago today, Hamid Karzai International Airport in Kabul, Afghanistan, was attacked by terrorists. 13 brave American service members, including Lance Corporal David Lee Espinoza of Rio Bravo, lost their lives as a result.

Today, my Laredo Outreach Coordinator, Melissa Peña, attended the groundbreaking ceremony for the Southern Hotel Affordable Housing Rehabilitation project.

Through this project, the Southern Hotel will be repurposed as affordable rental housing for Laredo residents.

Today, @samhsagov awarded the state of Texas $3,690,918 in federal funding for mental health care.

The funding was provided by the Community Mental Health Services Block Grant program. I will continue to fight for mental health care in our communities.

South Texas, please be careful as Tropical Storm Harold continues to make its way inland. Heavy rainfall and strong winds are expected, especially in Webb, Duval, and McMullen Counties.

If you are in need of immediate assistance, call 911.

weather.com/safety/hurricane…

It’s been one year since the Inflation Reduction Act (IRA) was signed into law. 

I helped pass the IRA to deliver real results for the families of TX-28. In just one year, the IRA dropped the annual cost of insulin from $1,705 to $420 for TX-28 seniors on Medicare.

Today, I announced $1,500,000 in federal funding for the Las Americas Roma Logistics & Industrial Park.

The funds will be used to develop the 328-acre Park’s infrastructure, including street development, drainage, lighting, gas lines, electricity, and telecommunications.

Today, I announced $1,150,000 in Congressionally directed funding for the El Cenizo Street Improvements Project.

The funds will be used to pave Morales Street and Hernandez Street in El Cenizo, which are vulnerable to flooding.

Today, I announced $1,000,000 in Congressionally directed funding for the Zacate Creek Restoration Project. The funds will be used to enhance and preserve Zacate Creek, ensuring Laredoans will continue to enjoy this natural geographical feature for generations to come.

Last night, I met a living legend: Hispanic comedian @georgelopez.

George, you put on a great show! Please visit again soon. You’re always welcome in Laredo.

I attended the D2 President’s Round Table meeting and visited with neighborhood associations in San Antonio.

I recently opened my new district office in San Antonio’s East Side and became a member of District 2. I appreciated the opportunity today to meet some new neighbors.

This morning, I joined the Alamo Colleges District for the ribbon cutting of the new Southside Education & Training Center.

A new addition to TX-28, this facility will make it convenient for San Antonio South Side residents to earn professional credentials for good-paying jobs.

Today, I announced $500,000 in Congressionally directed funding for the McMullen County fairgrounds.

The funds will be used to renovate the fairgrounds with improved lighting for parking and arena areas, an upgraded livestock show animal barn, and a new pavilion.

Today, I announced $1,300,000 in Congressionally directed funding for union apprenticeships in San Antonio. 

The funds will be used to purchase equipment and renovate workspaces for the Ironworks Local #66 through the City of San Antonio’s Ready to Work apprenticeship program.

Happy birthday to Bexar County Constable, Precinct 1, Ruben Tejeda! Thank you for allowing me to celebrate this special day with you in the company of friends and family, including former State Representative Joe Farias.

Here’s to many more years of life!

This evening, I had dinner with a couple of friends in San Antonio: Bexar County Clerk Lucy Adame-Clark and Bexar County District Clerk Gloria Martinez.

Together, we will continue to deliver for Bexar County!

One year ago, the Honoring Our PACT Act was signed into law.

I helped pass the #PACTAct to help South Texas veterans exposed to toxic fumes, burn pits, and Agent Orange get the healthcare they need. In Congress, I will continue to fight for our veterans.

Today, I announced $963,000 in Congressionally directed funding for new police cruisers in Guadalupe County.

The new vehicles will be equipped with improved handling features, GPS, and communications systems to help officers as they respond to emergency calls.

Today, U.S. Department of Labor’s Assistant Secretary for @VETS_DOL the Honorable James D. Rodriguez, and I announced $1,500,000 in federal funding for the American GI Forum National Veterans Outreach Program, Inc., in San Antonio. 

To our veterans, thank you for your service!

South Texas letter carriers work in the grueling Texas heat to deliver for our community. We must ensure they stay healthy and hydrated amidst triple digit temperatures that threaten heat exhaustion and heat stroke.

I stand with the working families of @NALC_National.

Today marks the one-year anniversary of the #CHIPSandScienceAct being signed into law.

I helped pass the #CHIPSAct last year to drive American innovation, create good-paying jobs, and to ensure the United States maintains its technological dominance.

Today, I announced $1,000,000 in funding for Duval County’s community centers. The funds will be used to renovate the centers with new air conditioning, heating units, roof replacements, generators, and kitchen equipment.
 
In Congress, I will continue to fight for Duval County.

Today, I joined @UTHealthSA’s School of Dentistry and @UTCenterlaredo to announce the new Bachelor of Science Degree in Dental Hygiene program.

This new program will forge the next generation of world-class dental hygienists right here in Laredo.

Carl

Nala (my Senior Legislative Assistant, Alicia Seagraves)

Esther (my Legislative Assistant, Matthew Gerson)

Sj (my DC Press Secretary, Arturo C. Olivarez)

Happy international cat day! Today, we celebrate our beloved feline friends. Here are the furry companions that bring joy to my family, my staff, and me:

Spooky

Sushi

Mr. McCow

Louie

I announced $2,850,148 in federal funding for broadband internet at @stcjaguars.

This federal investment for STC will ensure its 26,562 students have the broadband internet they need to learn, communicate, and access educational information as they work towards their degrees.

Today, my daughter, Christina, joined President Biden at the White House to recognize the 2022 World Series Champions, the @astros.

Christina had a chance to meet Starting Pitcher Justin Verlander and Manager Dusty Baker.

Thanks for having us, Mr. President. Go ‘Stros!

Today, I announced $1,000,000 in Congressionally directed funding for the new Jim Hogg County Emergency Operations Center (EOC).
 
The new EOC will enable first responders to provide Jim Hogg County’s residents more efficient emergency services and faster response times.

Today, I announced a $1,400,000 federal earmark for Laredo College’s Veterans Center of Excellence.
 
The Veterans Center of Excellence will serve as a one-stop facility offering a range of academic and career services to veterans and their dependents attending Laredo College.

Today is Purple Heart Day. On this day, we remember the many men and women who were wounded or killed in the line of duty.

We shall never forget their sacrifices and always honor their service to our country.

I stopped by Sweet Spot in Laredo today for some frozen yogurt. While there, I said hello to friends and fellow frozen yogurt connoisseurs. 

I hope everybody had a restful Sunday!

I’m saddened to hear that former Webb County Judge Andy Ramos passed away. I had the pleasure of calling Andy a friend. He will be greatly missed.

My prayers are with Judge Ramos, his wife, Adriana, and his family. May he rest in peace.

lmtonline.com/news/article/f…

Today, my San Antonio Outreach Coordinator, Aspen Walker, attended the City of Marion’s 87th Annual Sausage Supper hosted by the Marion Volunteer Fire Department and the Greater Marion Area Chamber of Commerce.
 
I hope everyone had a chance to enjoy the food and fun!

Happy 233rd birthday to the @USCG! Thank you for protecting our nation’s waters and ensuring our domestic security.

Semper Paratus!
I stand with the working families of South Texas. Thank you for your leadership in fighting for water breaks, @RepCasar!

Today, I announced a $1,000,000 federal earmark for the renovation of the Zapata County 4-H rodeo arena. The funds will be used to construct an all-weather roping arena roof, bleachers, and restroom facilities.

I will continue to fight for Zapata County in Congress.

I recently joined @RGISCLaredo for a symposium on the Justice40 Executive Order. Justice40 is a commitment to direct 40% of investments from the Inflation Reduction Act and the Bipartisan Infrastructure Law towards disadvantaged communities.

Thank you for having me!

This morning, @BLS_gov reported that 187,000 jobs were gained in July, and the unemployment rate remained low at 3.5%.

The American economy continues to demonstrate its strength and resilience. In Congress, I will continue to fight for a strong economy.

axios.com/2023/08/04/jobs-re…

Today, I joined Texas Transportation Commissioners Alex Meade and Alvin New, TxDOT engineers, and Ana Garcia from U.S. Senator John Cornyn’s office for a transportation roundtable.

I will continue to work with @TxDOT to improve South Texas’ transportation infrastructure.

Today, I announced $1,399,532 in federal funding for @txamiu.

An education is the great equalizer. In Congress, I will continue to prioritize our students’ education to ensure they are able to achieve their American Dream.

My Starr County office joined @Unitedwayofsotx for their annual Back-to-School “In Style” Shopping Spree. 150 middle school students received new school clothing, backpacks, personal hygiene items, school supplies, and haircuts.
 
Thank you for hosting an incredible event!

I stopped at Raising Cane’s today for some sweet tea. Thank you to the young workers for your exceptional service!

I hope everyone has a pleasant Wednesday.

The first seven months of 2023 have had the fastest returns for the S&P 500 and the Nasdaq Composite in decades. So far, the S&P 500 has grown by 19.5%, while the Nasdaq Composite has grown by 37.1%.
 
I will continue to fight in Congress for healthy growth in the stock market.

This past weekend, I joined a bipartisan Congressional Delegation to Germany to visit military installations. I had lunch with service members from Texas, including Daniel Batey, a 2011 graduate of Texas A&M University.

I will continue to fight for our military in Congress.

58 years ago today, Medicare and Medicaid were signed into law.

Medicare and Medicaid have offered health and financial stability for our seniors, persons with disabilities, and low-income Americans.

I will continue to fight to protect Medicare and Medicaid in Congress.
It was great to join you - thanks for having us!

¡Recuerda renovar tu Medicaid, Sur de Texas!
 
Mi oficina quiere recordarle sobre el nuevo proceso de cancelación de Medicaid que finaliza la inscripción continua, lo que podría afectar sus beneficios. Visite YourTexasBenefits.com para completar su renovación de Medicaid.

Remember to renew your Medicaid, South Texas!
 
My office wants to remind you about the new Medicaid unwinding process which ends continuous enrollment, potentially affecting your benefits. Visit YourTexasBenefits.com to complete your Medicaid renewal.

I joined @CNN to discuss the ongoing situation at our southern border.

The reality is we need the State of Texas to work with the federal government to secure the border.

lmtonline.com/local/article/…

Today, we celebrate 33 years of the Americans with Disabilities Act, a landmark law that continues to improve everyday accessibility for all Americans.

I will continue to fight for a more accessible future for South Texas.

If you’re a Veteran, you can file a claim by August 9, 2023, for PACT Act-related benefits backdated to last August.

I helped pass the PACT Act last year to support South Texas veterans. Be sure to file your claim soon!

Thank you to my friend, Arturo Dominguez, for visiting me today in my Washington, DC office. I presented his son, Arturito Dominguez, with a pin from the U.S. House of Representatives for his birthday.

Enjoy your time in our nation’s capital!

Today, I met with Honduran Foreign Minister Eduardo Enrique Reina.

Thank you for visiting me! I look forward to working with you to bring mutual success to the United States and Honduras.

Today, I spoke at @TheCHLI Future Leaders Conference in Washington, DC.

Thank you to CHLI Vice-Chair @MarioDB and CHLI President & CEO Mary Ann Gomez Orta for hosting me. I will always work to serve and inspire the next generation of Hispanic students in the United States.

Thank you to @CWAUnion Local 6143 President Geronimo Guerra for meeting with me today in Washington, DC.

I will continue to stand with the working families of South Texas.

Thank you to everyone who attended my new San Antonio district office grand opening ceremony. Over 200 attendees, including many community leaders, joined me for this momentous occasion.

It is an honor and a privilege to serve the 28th Congressional District of Texas.

I’m saddened to hear that Tony Bennett has passed away. Tony was an iconic musician whose music touched the country for decades.

Tony and his family are in my prayers. May he rest in peace.

Our students are the most important investment in our country, and I will always support them as they achieve their American Dream. I look forward to helping school districts nationwide access funding made possible by the Bipartisan Safer Communities Act.

lmtonline.com/local/article/…

Last month, border crossings sunk to their lowest level in over 2 years.

While there is still work to be done, I’m pleased to see progress has been made. I look forward to continuing our work with @DHSgov and @CBP to uphold law and order at our border.

politico.com/news/2023/07/18…

Three years ago today, we lost a civil rights icon in John Lewis. I had the honor of working with John, and the pleasure of calling him a friend.

Let us remind ourselves of John’s “Good Trouble” as we continue making our country a more equal, more perfect union every day.

I’m delayed on my way back home to Texas from Washington, DC, but a highlight of this trip is a rainbow before I leave.

I hope everyone has a good weekend!

Thank you to Elizabeth Bonker of Communication 4 ALL and Caden Larson of Children with Autism Deserve Education (CADE) for visiting me today.

As a Co-Chair of the Congressional Autism Caucus, I will continue to fight for federal resources for students with autism.

Thank you to Katherine Neigh, a rising senior from John B. Alexander High School in Laredo, for visiting me in Washington, DC today.

I will continue to support our South Texas students and help them achieve their American Dream.

We remember Lance Corporal David Lee Espinoza on what would have been his 22nd birthday.

We will always honor David’s service and sacrifices for our country. 

May he rest in peace, and may God be with his family.

My bill, the Water Infrastructure Enhancement Act of 2023, will establish a grant program within the EPA to replace old pipes and improve public water infrastructure.

I am committed to securing improved water infrastructure for South Texas.

lmtonline.com/local/article/…

Congratulations to my colleague, @gracenapolitano, on her retirement announcement. Congresswoman Napolitano has been a champion for the people of Southern California, and a national leader in the field of mental health care.

It has been a pleasure to serve with you, Grace!

This morning, @BLS_gov reported 209,000 jobs were added in June, and the unemployment rate remained low at 3.6%.

The American economy continues to demonstrate its strength and resiliency.

I’ll continue fighting for job creation, a healthy economy, and low prices in South Texas.

Thank you to U.S. District Judge Diana Saldana for organizing the Kazen Fellowship Program, and for inviting me to give the inaugural program address.

I look forward to fostering the next generation of legal minds for Laredo.

On July 4, 1776, the Second Continental Congress adopted the Declaration of Independence. 247 years later, we celebrate this day as the birth of our country. From my family to yours, Happy Independence Day!
 
May God bless you, and may God bless the United States of America.

Congratulations to the @spurs on the #1 pick in the NBA draft, Victor Wembanyama! Victor, welcome to South Texas.

Go Spurs Go!

espn.com/nba/story/_/id/3790…

Tonight, I voted for H.R. 1606, the Veteran Entrepreneurship Training Act of 2023, to codify the Boots to Business program into federal law. Veteran-owned businesses are a crucial component of the South Texas economy, and I will continue to support them.

It’s essential that South Texas letter carriers, who work in one of the hottest climates in the country, be at the very top of the list to receive new delivery vehicles equipped with air conditioning.
 
I’ll continue to fight for them and their families.
 
lmtonline.com/local/article/…

Congratulations to Jason Owens, the incoming 26th Chief of the United States Border Patrol.

I look forward to working with you to safeguard the American people, ensure our homeland security, and deliver for the men and women in green.

apnews.com/article/border-pa…

79 years ago on this day, Allied forces landed along the French coastline in Normandy to fight Nazi Germany and pave the way to victory in WWII. On the anniversary of D-Day, we remember those who took part in that historic invasion, and honor those who did not return home.

My heartfelt congratulations to Acting Director of @ICEgov Tae Johnson on his retirement announcement. I have had the pleasure of working with Acting Director Johnson, and I am grateful for his 31+ years of service to the agency.

nbcnews.com/news/amp/rcna878…

The Bipartisan Budget Agreement has now officially been signed into law.

I applaud my colleagues in Congress for delivering this legislation at a crucial moment for the economic stability and prosperity of all Americans.

reuters.com/world/us/biden-s…

This morning, the Bureau of Labor Statistics reported 339,000 jobs were gained in May, and the unemployment rate remained low at 3.7%.

The American economy continues to demonstrate its strength and resiliency.

cnbc.com/2023/06/02/jobs-rep…

Thank you to Chief of Operations for Border Patrol HQ LEOP David BeMiller, Laredo Sector Chief Patrol Agent Joel Martinez, and Pete Salinas, Adjutant to Chief Martinez, for visiting me in Washington, DC this week.

I will continue to fight for you in Congress!

This pivotal legislation will act as a safeguard for our American economy and avert a potential financial crisis.

(3/3)

After engaging in thoughtful discussions with my fellow colleagues, irrespective of their party affiliations, I am heartened to witness a spirit of compromise prevailing.

(2/3)

This evening, I voted in favor of the Bipartisan Budget Agreement.

We should never allow the well-being of the American people to become a bargaining chip in partisan politics.

(1/3)

This Memorial Day, let us come together as a grateful community and ensure that the sacrifices of our fallen heroes are never forgotten. May we continue to honor their legacy by embracing liberty, unity, and compassion in our daily lives. 

Today, we stand united in remembrance.

Today marks the 1-Year anniversary of the tragic Uvalde shooting at Robb Elementary School. This day is filled with sadness, loss, and grief. We remember the innocent lives taken too soon and the pain endured by their loved ones.

Uvalde, you’re forever in my prayers.

What a treat it was to meet today with Al Smith and Rayford Carter from @NRLCA in my Washington, DC office. 

Many thanks Al and Rayford for the visit - rest assured, you and your members can count on my support! 

#nrlca #tx28 #hardworkrealresults

Rest in Peace to Jim Brown, a legendary football player who was considered one of the greatest in history. He was also a champion for civil rights who organized a meeting of the nation’s top Black athletes, dubbed “The Cleveland Summit.”

He and his family are in my prayers.

This morning, I met with Dr. Scott Kercheville, an anesthesiologist in San Antonio. We discussed improving health care for South Texas.
 
Thank you for visiting me! I look forward to continuing our important work.

Congratulations @spurs for winning the 2023 NBA draft lottery with the Number 1 overall pick.

Victor Wembanyama, you’re almost home. Go Spurs Go!

Join me this Saturday at Laredo College for GirlCon Texas! GirlCon is a free conference for girls interested in tech careers.

To register, click the link below:

eventbrite.com/e/girlcon-tex…

This morning, I met with Michael Scaief, Alex Meade, and Erik Ommen from the Independent Bankers Association of Texas (IBAT) in my Washington, DC office.
 
Thank you for stopping by – I will continue to fight for independent Texas bankers in Washington.

This morning, I joined @cspanwj to discuss the federal debt limit and border policy. Thank you to host John McArdle for speaking with me.

Click the link below to watch a recording of this morning’s interview:

c-span.org/video/?528105-5/r…

Today, on Peace Officers Memorial Day, we pause to honor and remember the brave men and women in blue who made the ultimate sacrifice in the line of duty.

Join me in taking a moment to reflect on the sacrifices made by these heroes.

Happy Mother's Day to all the incredible moms across this country. Today is a day to celebrate and honor the selfless love, care, and sacrifices that mothers make every day.

To my mother, Odilia ✝️, my mother-in-law, Esperanza, and my wife, Imelda, today is your day. I love you!

Today, in Washington, DC, I met with Marco A. Villarreal, Jr., from Union Pacific. Marco is also from Laredo.

It was good to see you. I’ll continue supporting our South Texas rail workers.

Today, Border Patrol apprehended two large groups of undocumented migrants: a group of more than 230 in Ajo, Arizona, and another of more than 250 near Campo, California.

Thank you to our men and women in green who are tirelessly working to secure our border.

This morning, according to @CBP, @TxDPS ceased their operation of mechanical inspections at southern border ports of entry in Brownsville.

This is welcome news, and I’m glad to see we’re getting international trade back on track in South Texas.

This morning, I spoke with @ShannonBream about Title 42 and the border. Thank you for having me!

With Title 42 set to expire this coming Thursday, I will continue to work with @DHSgov, @CBP, and our border communities to uphold law and order at our southern border.

Thank you @AnaCabrera for hosting me this morning to discuss the ongoing situation at our southern border. 

We need law and order at the border, but we must treat migrants with the dignity and respect they deserve.

This morning, @BLS_gov reported 253,000 jobs were added in the month of April, and unemployment remained low at 3.4%.

This is encouraging news for our economy.

I will continue to fight for good-paying jobs and low prices for South Texas.

wsj.com/articles/april-jobs-…
